# iOS — {{ project_name }}

Swift 6 + SwiftUI with MVVM architecture. Requires Mac with Xcode 26 for building.

## Quick Reference

- **Generate project**: `task ios:generate-project` (runs xcodegen)
- **Build**: `task ios:build`
- **Test**: `task ios:test`
- **Min iOS**: 17.0 | **Swift**: 6.0 | **Xcode**: 26

## Architecture (MVVM)

```
{{ project_slug }}/
  DI/            → DependencyContainer (@Observable)
  Navigation/    → AppRouter + Route enum
  Data/
    Network/     → APIClient (async/await) + APIEndpoint
    Storage/     → Keychain TokenStorage (actor) + SwiftData models
    Repository/  → Protocol + Impl pattern
  Domain/Model/  → Codable DTOs
  UI/
    Theme/       → AppTheme (from design tokens)
    Auth/        → LoginView + LoginViewModel
    Examples/    → ExampleListView + ExampleListViewModel
    Common/      → LoadingView, ErrorView, PrimaryButton
```

## MVVM Pattern

- **ViewModel**: `@Observable` class with `ViewState` enum
- **ViewState**: enum — `idle`, `loading`, `success`, `error(String)`
- **View**: SwiftUI `View` structs with `@Bindable` ViewModel
- **DI**: Protocol-based via `DependencyContainer`, injected via `.environment()`
- **Navigation**: `NavigationStack` + `Route` enum

## Conventions

- One ViewModel per screen, initialized with repository dependencies
- Repositories are protocols with `Impl` classes
- APIClient is an `actor` for thread safety
- TokenStorage uses Keychain via Security framework
- Local caching via SwiftData (`@Model` classes in `Data/Storage/`)
- Tests use mock repositories conforming to protocols
- All network calls use `async`/`await`

## Key Files

- `DI/DependencyContainer.swift` — all dependency wiring
- `Data/Network/APIClient.swift` — URLSession-based, generic `request<T>` method
- `Data/Storage/TokenStorage.swift` — Keychain-backed, actor-isolated
- `Data/Storage/CachedExample.swift` — SwiftData model for local caching
- `UI/Theme/AppTheme.swift` — colors + spacing from design tokens
- `project.yml` — XcodeGen spec (Mac only)
